<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-580-409  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 580 409.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  Oct 11 1990 v38 n19 p127(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Salary survey: pay increases are harder to come by this year.andO;(electronic engineers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Van Tyle, Sherrie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Salary raises for design engineers in 1990 are not expected to belarge.andP;  Raises earned in the past 12 months are lower than raisesearned in the preceding 12-month period.andP;  'Electronic Design'readers responded to a survey taken in Aug 1990.andP;  The 354respondents were typically male, 39.7 years old, have 13.7 yearsof engineering experience and earn $51,676 annually.andP;  Engineerstend to make less money than doctors, lawyers and scientists withan equal number of years in the profession.andP;  Salary ceilings canhave a negative impact on morale and productivity and may causemany engineers to leave the technical field and join the higherpaying ranks of management.andP;  Approximately 39 percent of thesurvey respondents felt their salary had hit the top and would notgo significantly higher.andP;  The average plateau was $59,492.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DesignEngineeringSurveySalaryJob Satisfaction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>